			<div class="content" id="post-content-4820543">
									

<p><strong>Seeking Greenlights:</strong> Yes<br />
<strong>Page Type:</strong> SCP Article<br />
<strong>Genre:</strong> Weird, Existential</p>
<p><strong>Elevator Pitch:</strong> Humanoid emissary from another dimension arrives with existential dread of own worthlessness in a greater plan to gather data on the multiverse. It is one of many that exist, though none share the same appearance or destiny in the same universe. Each remembers the sentient entity called the “Frequency” who brought them there, which can transmute sound waves into matter (and vice-versa); even capable of compressing and accelerating sound waves to transcend dimensional boundaries. The Frequency has also grown interested in our dimension.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Read&nbsp;More</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide&nbsp;Section</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Central Narrative:</strong> Subject was sent extradimensionally to complete its goal of understanding our universe by will of a greater entity known only as “The Frequency”. The Frequency is a sentient, sound-based entity that seeks greater knowledge of the multiverse, dispersing various humanoid-like figures across timelines, each with specific missions and purposes. Both mental and physiological limitations instilled in each one by their creator are intended to control their decisions to minimize potential rogue behaviors. If any of these individuals outright refuse orders, the Frequency will remotely terminate them and create another to fill its role.<br />
The focus of this SCP article is emphasizing the emotional struggle one such subject, and how they are abundantly aware of their own worthlessness and inescapable fate. The narrative arc will be expressed through extensive documentation and conducted interviews with the humanoid detailing how the experience has damaged the subject both mentally and emotionally, feeling empty and hollow from the burden of their intended purpose. It knows it is expected to die someday like all the others, considered no more valuable in the eyes of the Frequency than how the SCP Foundation values D-Class personnel. Despite this, the entity cannot bring itself to turn on its creator, with desperate hope of a slim possibility it may live to see the Frequency’s plans through. These hopes, unfortunately, fall on deaf ears.</p>
<p><strong>Hook/Attention-Grabber:</strong> With this narrative-driven SCP article, an emissary from another world is not empowered by its defined sense of purpose, rather burdened by it instead.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Tags:</strong> <em>acoustic, extradimensional, euclid, humanoid, knowledge, language, sapient, sentient</em></p>

