<p>Heya, I'll stop by and share my thoughts.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+Let's&nbsp;do&nbsp;it!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-Yeet</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>Amnesiac humanoid emissary from another dimension arrives with existential dread of own worthlessness in a greater plan unbeknownst to anyone.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>If it's amnesiac, how does it feel dread of some greater plan? With wording like that, it shouldn't even have knowledge of this greater plan.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>It is one of many that exist, though never in the same universe.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Going by the multiverse theory, every alternate universe (or at least most) would/should already have a different version of every person, so this really shouldn't be that unique.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>This narrative is not about the creature; the creature is the side character to something else’s story.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This part interests me but is never expanded upon. Although, 'pawn to bigger plan' stories aren't exactly unique, but a higher being using every multiverse version of one person for a greater plan certainly is unique, but that's never properly explored or explained here.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>however they exist solely to accomplish some task for some master plan they remain unaware of, or just to die.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Sorry to repeat myself so often, but please tell us what this plan is.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>the creature is self-aware to be unimportant and expendable. .</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Again, with amnesia, how does it know this?</p>
<p>Also, this may just be a personal thing, but I greatly dislike amnesia as a plot device. It always feels like such a lazy way to create mystery. I feel like nearly every amnesia-based plot device would be much stronger if the entities/characters just..withheld information?</p>
<p>'I can't remember my backstory but I conveniently know how everything works' ceases to interest me.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Only hint to past is anomalous staticky screams it deems familiar made audible whenever near electronic devices.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Also not explored in this pitch.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>It is considered of extradimensional origin, but it is incapable of extradimensional travel.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Because something put it in every universe, it didn't go there on its own.</p>
<p>All in all, I can feel a grand, underlying plot and a desire to see it through, but there's very little given here to make heads nor tail of it.</p>
<p>Apologies of this was harsh, but every detail here will need significant expansion if you want to garner interest.</p>
<p>I hope I helped and I bid you a lovely day!</p>
<p>👍👍👍</p>
</div>
</div>
