<p>This is conceptually interesting, and I’d definitely wanna fine tune the concept of the anomaly but first.</p>
<p>You’re saying this is a narrative SCP but I’m failing to see the narrative arc. Spell it out, not the mystery, but the logistics of the story.</p>
<p>Also, characterization would be key here as otherwise the reader won’t much care that this being is facing an existential dread.</p>
<p>Additionally, think this would be better without the doom of the Frequency’s awakening. It distracts from the existential horror to some extent&#8230; lots of eldritch beings on the wiki that are Big Bad Cthulhu types&#8230; but what if it didn’t have an agenda except knowledge? Focusing instead of the experience of the pawn</p>

