<p>Hello, let's get down to it.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The creature's origins here are fascinating. I myself have been working on a group of inter-dimensional journalists called the Wandsmen with similar goals to your &quot;Frequency&quot;, though they have more broad methods.</p>
<p>So, a lot of this concept will land on the emotional weight of your skip being functionally a slave to this entity and very aware that it is utterly disposable.</p>
<p>I admit, crossovers with Series 1 skips are often frowned upon, so I might see if there are some more modern or original anomalies you could replace 187 with.</p>
<p>Honestly so far though I like this a lot, though you probably want to tip your hand as to a few more details about the Frequency early on, so the concept can be examined and iterated upon.</p>
<p>Also, you might want to try reading the concept aloud. I know that's odd, but even at the concept stage readability is a big deal for getting greenlit and there were some sections of this, especially in the description that left me confused.</p>
<p>Overall I think this idea has legs and I look forward to seeing later versions of it.</p>
</div>
